headline: 3 Reasons HRL is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, Hormel Foods’s shares (currently trading at $23.91) have posted a disappointing 19.5% loss, well below the S&P 500’s 22.7% gain. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
